onomist of Health Care Wins John Bates Clark Medal|url=https://www.chronicle.com/blogs/ticker/mit-economist-of-health-care-wins-john-bates-clark-medal/42712|publisher= The Chronicle of Higher Education}}</ref>\n* [[Stanley Fischer]], economist and the vice chair of the U.S. Federal Reserve System\n* [[Robert Fogel]], Nobel Prize (1993)\n* [[David D. Friedman]], son of Milton Friedman\n* [[Milton Friedman]], Nobel Prize (1976)<ref name=\"nobel1\">{{cite web |title=Milton Friedman on nobelprize.org |url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/economics/laureates/1976/ |year=1976 |publisher=Nobel Prize |accessdate=February 20, 2008}}</ref>\n* [[Alan Greenspan]], former Chair of the US [[Federal Reserve Bank]]<ref>{{cite news|author1= [[Benjamin M. Friedman]]|title=Chairman Greenspan\u2019s Legacy|url=http://www.nybooks.com/articles/archives/2008/mar/20/chairman-greenspans-legacy |work= [[New York Review of Books]] | volume = 55 | issue=4|date=March 20, 2008}}</ref>\n* [[John Harsanyi]], Nobel Prize (1994)\n* [[Leonid Hurwicz]], Nobel Prize (2007)\n* [[Daniel Kahneman]], Nobel Prize (2002)<ref name=\"Daniel Kahneman - Biographical\">{{cite web|title=Daniel Kahneman - Biographical|url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/economic-sciences/laureates/2002/kahneman-bio.html|publisher= Nobel Prize}}</ref>\n* [[Steven Kaplan (economist)|Steven Kaplan]]\n* [[Lawrence Klein]], Nobel Prize (1980)<ref name=\"Lawrence Klein (1920-2013)\">{{cite web|title=Lawrence Klein (1920-2013)|url=https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/lawrence-klein|publisher= Jewish Virtual Library}}</ref>\n* [[Paul Krugman]], Nobel Prize (2008)<ref name=\"Paul Krugman - Facts\">{{cite web|title=Paul Krugman - Facts|url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/economic-sciences/laureates/2008/krugman-facts.html|publisher= Nobel Prize}}</ref>\n* [[Simon Kuznets]], Nobel Prize (1971)\n* [[Wassily Leontief]], Nobel Prize (1973)\n* [[Harry Markowitz]], Nobel Prize (1990)\n* [[Eric Maskin]], Nobel Prize (2007)<ref nam