rist\n* [[Daron Acemoglu]], economist, of Armenian descent\n* [[Taner Ak\u00e7am]], [[University of Minnesota]] professor, historian specializing in the [[Armenian Genocide]]<ref>{{Cite news|url=http://www.chgs.umn.edu/histories/turkishArmenian/|title=Narratives and Testimonies|work=College of Liberal Arts {{!}} University of Minnesota|access-date=2018-06-02|language=en}}</ref>\n* [[\u0130lhan Aksay]], professor, Princeton University<ref>[http://chemeng.princeton.edu/people/aksay.shtml Chemical Engineering - People - Ilhan A. Aksay<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071231030047/http://chemeng.princeton.edu/people/aksay.shtml |date=2007-12-31 }}</ref>\n* [[\u00d6zalp Babao\u011flu]], professor of computer science at [[University of Bologna]]\n* [[Ci\u011fdem Bal\u0131m]]\n* [[As\u0131m Orhan Barut]], [[University of Colorado at Boulder|University of Colorado-Boulder]] physicist<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://phys.lsu.edu/~jdowling/barut.html|title=Asim Orhan Barut|website=phys.lsu.edu|access-date=2018-06-02}}</ref>\n*[[Mine \u00c7etinkaya-Rundel]], associate professor of the practice in statistics at [[Duke University]]\n* [[Faruk G\u00fcl]], Professor of Economics, Princeton University<ref>[http://www.econ.princeton.edu/faculty/permfaculty.html Economics: Permanent Faculty Members<!-- Bot generated title -->] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080101161058/http://www.econ.princeton.edu/faculty/permfaculty.html |date=2008-01-01 }}</ref>\n* [[Feza G\u00fcrsey]], mathematician and physicist\n* [[M. \u015e\u00fckr\u00fc Hanio\u011flu]], Professor of Near Eastern Studies, [[Princeton University]]\n* [[Alp Ikizler]], nephrologist, holder of the Catherine McLaughlin Hakim chair in Medicine at [[Vanderbilt University School of Medicine]]\n* [[Merve Kavak\u00e7\u0131]], [[George Washington University]] [[Professor]] and former [[Virtue Party|Fazilet Party]] [[Parliament of England|Parliamentarian]] exiled from [[Turkey]] for v