ark Harris]], novelist and biographer\n* [[Joseph Heller]], author of ''[[Catch-22]]''<ref>Loveday, Veronica. \"Joseph Heller.\" Joseph Heller (9781429802864) (2005): 1\u20132. History Reference Center. EBSCO. Web. Dec 1, 2010</ref>\n* [[Lillian Hellman]], playwright, screenwriter, memoirist, novelist \n* [[Mark Helprin]], novelist and journalist \n* [[Christopher Hitchens]], literary critic and political activist<ref>[http://observer.guardian.co.uk/worldview/story/0,11581,683899,00.html Look who's talking] ''The Observer'', 14 April 2002</ref><ref>Hitch-22, page 352.</ref>\n* [[Russell Hoban]], fantasy and science fiction writer\n* [[Laura Z. Hobson]], novelist\n* [[Dara Horn]], novelist\n* [[Irving Howe]], literary critic<ref>Rodden, John and Goffman, Ethan (2010). \"Chronology\". ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=DCwaO17isQMC&pg=PR15&dq=Irving+Howe+Horenstein&hl=en&redir_esc=y Politics and the Intellectual: Conversations With Irving Howe]''. West Lafayette, IN: Purdue University Press. {{ISBN|9781557535511}}. Pg. xv.</ref>\n* [[Fannie Hurst]], novelist and short story writer\n* [[Fishel Jacobs]], Jewish law, short story, children's writer [[Two Kings]]\n* [[Rona Jaffe]], novelist\n* [[Erica Jong]], novelist and poet, best known for second-wave feminist work ''[[Fear of Flying (novel)|Fear of Flying]]'' (1973)\n* [[Roger Kahn]], author of ''[[The Boys of Summer (book)|The Boys of Summer]]'' (1972)\n* [[Bob Kane]], co-creator of Batman\n* [[Garson Kanin]], playwright, screenwriter\n* [[Bel Kaufman]], novelist, granddaughter of Sholom Aleichem\n* [[Faye Kellerman]], mystery writer\n* [[Jonathan Kellerman]], mystery and suspense writer, psychologist\n* [[William Melvin Kelley]], novelist and short-story writer\n* [[Jamaica Kincaid]], novelist and essayist\n* [[Cyril M. Kornbluth]], science fiction writer\n* [[Jerzy Kosinski]], author of ''[[The Painted Bird]]''\n* [[Nicole Krauss]], best known for her three novels, ''[[Man Walks Into a Room]]'' (2002), ''[[The His