stery works<ref>{{cite news| url=http://www.thejc.com/arts/books/15550/stay-cold-blooded-sun | work=Jewish Chronicle (London) | title=Stay cold-blooded in the sun | accessdate=2012-04-02}}</ref>\n* [[Mark Obama Ndesandjo]], author, half-brother of President [[Barack Obama]]<ref>{{cite news| url=http://us.cnn.com/video/?/video/world/2009/11/18/vause.china.obama.brother.cnn | work=CNN | title=CNN.com Video | accessdate=2010-05-08}}</ref>\n* [[Tillie Olsen]], first-wave feminist writer, best known for her novella ''[[Tell Me a Riddle]]'', title story in a collection of four short stories and winner of the O. Henry Prize in 1961\n* [[Cynthia Ozick]], short story writer, novelist, and essayist<ref>[http://topics.nytimes.com/topics/reference/timestopics/people/o/cynthia_ozick/index.html Articles about Cynthia Ozick], ''[[New York Times]]''</ref><ref name=brockes>Emma Brockes. [https://www.theguardian.com/culture/2011/jul/04/cynthia-ozick-life-writing-interview \"A life in writing: Cynthia Ozick\"], ''The Guardian'', 2 July 2011</ref>\n* [[Grace Paley]], short story writer and poet; finalist for both National Book Award and Pulitzer Prize\n* [[Sara Paretsky]], mystery writer\n* [[Dorothy Parker]], humorist, poet and short story writer\n* [[Harvey Pekar]], comic book writer, music critic\n* [[S. J. Perelman]], humorist, essayist, screenwriter\n* [[Joan Peters]], author of ''[[From Time Immemorial]]''\n* [[Jodi Picoult]], novelist<ref>''[[Jewish Chronicle]]'', April 27, 2007 p.50: \"The Jodi Picoult mystery\"</ref>\n* [[Daniel Pinkwater]], children's and young adult author\n* [[Belva Plain]], novelist\n* [[Chaim Potok]], author and rabbi\n* [[Ayn Rand]], novelist and founder of [[Objectivism (Ayn Rand)|Objectivism]]<ref>{{harvnb|Heller|2009|pp=3\u20135}}; {{harvnb|Britting|2004|pp=2\u20133}}; {{harvnb|Burns|2009|pp=9}}</ref>\n* [[Lea Bayers Rapp]],<ref>{{cite web\n |url=http://www.kensingtonbooks.com/catalog.cfm?dest=dir&linkon=subsection&linkid=1775 \n |title=Lea Bayers Rap