ond]], evolutionary biologist and biogeographer\n* [[Carl Djerassi]], contraceptive pill\n* [[Brian David Dynlacht]], biochemist, TFIID (1991) and CP110 (2002)\n* [[Victor Dzau]], President of the United States National Academy of Medicine\n* [[Gerald Edelman]], biologist, Nobel Prize (1972)<ref name=\"Nobel Prize\">{{cite web |url=http://nobelprize.org/medicine/laureates/1972/index.html| title=The Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine 1972 |accessdate=2007-09-27}}</ref>\n* [[Gertrude Elion]], drug development, Nobel Prize (1988)<ref>{{cite book|last1=Wasserman|first1=Elga R.|title=The door in the dream : conversations with eminent women in science|publisher=Joseph Henry Press|isbn=0-309-06568-2|page=[https://archive.org/details/doorindream00elga/page/46 46]|url-access=registration|url=https://archive.org/details/doorindream00elga/page/46}}</ref>\n* [[Joseph Erlanger]], physiologist, Nobel Prize (1945)\n* [[Edmond H. Fischer]], biochemist, Nobel Prize (1992) (Jewish father)\n* [[Judah Folkman]], cancer angiogenesis\n* [[Rosalind Franklin]], X-ray crystallographer\n* [[Casimir Funk]], vitamins\n* [[Robert F. Furchgott]], pharmacologist, Nobel Prize (1998)\n* [[Alfred G. Gilman]], biochemist, Nobel Prize (1994)<ref>{{cite web|title=The Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine 1994|url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/1994/|accessdate=22 January 2016|publisher=Nobel Media AB}}</ref>\n* [[Joseph L. Goldstein]], molecular geneticist, Nobel Prize (1985)\n* [[Stephen Jay Gould]], evolutionary biologist and writer\n* [[Paul Greengard]], neuroscientist, Nobel Prize (2000)\n* [[Rachel Haurwitz]], biochemist and structural biologist\n* [[Michael Heidelberger]], immunochemist\n* [[Horace Hodes]], pediatrician\n* [[Jerome Horowitz]], AZT\n* [[H. Robert Horvitz]], biologist, Nobel Prize (2002)<ref>{{cite web|title=H. Robert Horvitz \u2013 Nobel diploma|url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/2002/horvitz-diploma.html|website=Nobel Pri