ler-Urey experiment\n* [[Arthur J. Moss]], cardiologist\n* [[Hermann Joseph Muller|Hermann Muller]], geneticist, Nobel Prize (1946)\n* [[Daniel Nathans]], microbiologist, Nobel Prize (1978)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/1978/|title=The Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine 1978|publisher=NobelPrize.org}}</ref>\n* [[Marshall Nirenberg]], genetic code, Nobel Prize (1968)\n* [[Gregory Pincus]], contraceptive pill\n* [[Karl H. Pribram|Karl Pribram]], neurologist\n* [[Stanley Prusiner]], neurologist, Nobel Prize (1997)\n* [[Martin Rodbell]], biochemist, Nobel Prize (1994)\n* [[Ora Mendelsohn Rosen]], insulin receptor\n* [[Albert Sabin]], oral polio vaccine\n* [[Jonas Salk]], polio vaccine<ref>{{Cite web|title = About Jonas Salk \u2013 Salk Institute for Biological Studies|url = http://www.salk.edu/about/history-of-salk/jonas-salk/|website = Salk Institute for Biological Studies|access-date = February 22, 2016}}</ref>\n* [[Albert Schatz (scientist)|Albert Schatz]], streptomycin\n* [[B\u00e9la Schick]], diphtheria test\n* [[Rudolf Schoenheimer]], radioactive tracers\n* [[Werner Spitz]], forensic pathologist\n* [[Leo Sternbach]], valium\n* [[Howard Temin]], reverse transcriptase, Nobel Prize (1975)<ref>[http://nobelprize.org/medicine/laureates/1975/temin-autobio.html Howard M. Temin \u2013 Autobiography]. nobelprize.org</ref>\n* [[Max Tishler]], synthetic vitamins\n* [[Harold Varmus]], virologist, Nobel Prize (1989)<ref>{{cite web|url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/1989/varmus-lecture.html|title=Harold E. Varmus \u2013 Nobel Lecture: Retroviruses and Oncogenes I|work=nobelprize.org}}</ref>\n* [[Selman Waksman]], streptomycin, Nobel Prize (1952)\n* [[George Wald]], retina pigmentation, Nobel Prize (1967).<ref name=WaldNobelPrize>{{cite web|last1=The Nobel Foundation|title=The Nobel Prize in Physiology or Medicine 1967|url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/medicine/laureates/1967/|website=Nobelprize.org|p