mist, Nobel Prize (1985)<ref>[http://www.buffalonews.com/obituaries/article605235.ece Dr. Herbert Hauptman, Nobel Prize winner, is dead at 94]</ref>\n* [[Rachel Haurwitz]], biochemist and structural biologist\n* [[Roald Hoffmann]] (1937\u2013), chemist and writer, Nobel Prize winner (1981)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.roaldhoffmann.com/pn/modules.php?op=modload&name=Sections&file=index&req=viewarticle&artid=11&page=1 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2007-10-31 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080119031913/http://www.roaldhoffmann.com/pn/modules.php?op=modload&name=Sections&file=index&req=viewarticle&artid=11&page=1 |archivedate=2008-01-19 }} \"Roald Hoffmann was born in a Polish Jewish family in Zloczow, Poland\"</ref>\n* [[Martin Kamen]], carbon-14<ref>{{cite journal|author=Arnold, James|title=Obituary: Martin David Kamen|journal=Physics Today|date=May 2003|volume=56|issue=5|pages=74\u201375|url=http://scitation.aip.org/content/aip/magazine/physicstoday/article/56/5/10.1063/1.1583542|doi=10.1063/1.1583542|bibcode = 2003PhT....56e..74A }}</ref>\n* [[Martin Karplus]], theoretical chemist\n* [[Phoebus Levene]], nucleic acid pioneer\n* [[Bruce H. Lipshutz]], organometallic chemist\n* [[Jacob A. Marinsky]], discovered promethium<ref name=\"Jacob Marinsky, 87, Dies; Isolated Promethium Ions\">{{cite news|title=Jacob Marinsky, 87, Dies; Isolated Promethium Ions|url=https://www.nytimes.com/2005/09/08/us/jacob-marinsky-87-dies-isolated-promethium-ions.html|publisher= New York Times}}</ref>\n* [[Yurii Sh. Matros]], Jewish-American chemist and chemical engineer, developer of Matros reactor, founder of Matros Technologies Inc.\n* [[Alexander Pines]], physical chemist, Wolf Prize (1991)<ref name=\"THE 1991 WOLF FOUNDATION PRIZE IN CHEMISTRY\">{{cite web|title=THE 1991 WOLF FOUNDATION PRIZE IN CHEMISTRY|url=http://www.wolffund.org.il/index.php?dir=site&page=winners&cs=57&language=eng|publisher= Wolf Foundation}}</ref>\n* [[Martin Pope]], physical chem