11|author=Jack Schofield|newspaper=[[The Guardian]]|author-link=Jack Schofield (journalist)}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url = http://amturing.acm.org/award_winners/mccarthy_0239596.cfm | title = A. M. Turing award: John McCarthy, United States - 1971 | publisher = ACM | accessdate = September 5, 2012}}</ref>\n* [[Emil Post]], logician \n* [[Herbert Robbins]], statistician \n* [[Abraham Robinson]], nonstandard analysis \n* [[Arthur Rubin]], mathematician\n* [[Shlomo Sawilowsky]], statistician\n* [[Jack Minker]], database logic<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.jhsgw.org/exhibitions/online/voices/activists-and-supporters/dr-jack-minker|title=Dr. Jack Minker|date=|author=Jewish Historical Society of Greater Washington}}</ref>\n* [[Marvin Minsky]], artificial intelligence, neural nets, Turing Award (1969); co-founder of [[Massachusetts Institute of Technology|MIT]]'s AI laboratory<ref>{{cite news|url=http://jewishjournal.com/culture/lifestyle/obituaries/181634/|title=Artificial intelligence pioneer Marvin Minsky dies; 88|date=Jan 26, 2016|author=Scott Malone|newspaper=[[The Jewish Journal of Greater Los Angeles]]}}</ref>\n* [[John von Neumann]] (born Neumann J\u00e1nos Lajos), Hungarian-American computer scientist, mathematician and economist<ref>{{cite magazine|url=http://content.time.com/time/magazine/article/0,9171,21839,00.html|title=John von Neumann|date=Mar 1, 1999|author=Nathan Myhrvold|magazine=[[Time (magazine)|Time]]|quote=Born to prosperous Jewish parents in Budapest in 1903|author-link=Nathan Myhrvold}}</ref>\n* [[Seymour Papert]], South African-born co-inventor &mdash; with [[Wally Feurzeig]] and [[Cynthia Solomon]] &mdash; of the [[Logo (programming language)|Logo]] programming language<ref>{{cite web|url=https://forward.com/culture/346666/remembering-seymour-papert-revolutionary-socialist-and-father-of-ai/|title=Remembering Seymour Papert: Revolutionary Socialist and Father of A.I.|date=Aug 3, 2016|author=Benjamin Ivry|publisher=[[The Forward]]|author-link=Benjamin Ivry}}</ref>\n* [[Ken Perlin]], [[Perlin noise]]\n* [[Alan J. Perlis]], compilers, Turing Award (1966)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://amturing.acm.org/award_winners/perlis_0132439.cfm|title=A. J. Perlis|date=|author=David Nofre|publisher=[[Association for Computing Machinery]] (ACM)}}</ref>\n* [[Lawrence Rabiner]], [[Digital signal processing]], [[Speech processing]]\n* [[Frank Rosenblatt]], invented an artificial intelligence program called \"[[Frank Rosenblatt#Perceptron|Perceptrons]]\" (1960)<ref name=\"Hyping Artificial Intelligence, Yet Again\">{{cite magazine|title=Hyping Artificial Intelligence, Yet Again|url=https://www.newyorker.com/tech/elements/hyping-artificial-intelligence-yet-again|magazine= The New Yorker}}</ref>\n* [[Azriel Rosenfeld]], [[image analysis]]<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.washingtonpost.com/archive/local/2004/02/27/azriel-rosenfeld-dies-at-73/572122c6-a7dd-46d1-a8d6-36e783587eae/|title=Azriel Rosenfeld Dies at 73|date=Feb 27, 2004|author=Patricia Sullivan|newspaper=[[The Washington Post]]}}</ref>\n* [[Bruce Schneier]], cryptographer, author, founder of [[BT Managed Security Solutions|Counterpane Internet Security, Inc.]]\n* [[Ben Shneiderman]], human-computer interaction, information visualization<ref>{{cite web|url=https://forward.com/culture/186539/the-jewish-inspiration-that-guided-photographers-o/|title=The Jewish Inspiration That Guided Photographers of Magnum|date=Nov 3, 2013|author=Menachem Wecker|publisher=[[The Forward]]}}</ref>\n* [[Herbert A. Simon]], cognitive and computer scientist, Turing Award (1975)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://amturing.acm.org/award_winners/simon_1031467.cfm|title=Herbert (\"Herb\") Alexander Simon|author=Hunter Heyck|publisher=[[Association for Computing Machinery]] (ACM)}}</ref>\n* [[Abraham Sinkov]], cryptanalyst, [[NSA Hall of Honor]] (1999)\n* [[Gustave Solomon]], [[mathematician]] and [[electrical engineer]] who was one of the founders of the algebraic theory of [[error detection and correction]]<