ecker|publisher= Jewish Virtual Library}}</ref>\n* [[Ben Bernanke]], former Chair of the US [[Federal Reserve Bank]]<ref>{{cite web| url = http://www.brookings.edu/about/media-relations/news-releases/2014/0203-bernanke-hutchins-center | title = Federal Reserve Chairman Ben Bernanke to Join Economic Studies at Brookings |publisher = Brookings | date = February 3, 2014 | accessdate = February 3, 2014}}</ref>\n* [[Walter Block]], Harold E. Wirth Endowed Chair in Economics at [[Loyola University New Orleans|Loyola University]] in New Orleans<ref name=\"The Libertarian Big Tent\">{{cite web|title=The Libertarian Big Tent|url=https://www.lewrockwell.com/2006/12/walter-e-block/the-libertarian-big-tent/|publisher= LewRockwell}}</ref>\n* [[Arthur F. Burns]], economic adviser to the Eisenhower administration (1953) and Chairman to the Federal Reserve (1970)<ref name=\"Arthur F. Burns Is Dead at 83; A Shaper of Economic Policy\">{{cite news|title=Arthur F. Burns Is Dead at 83; A Shaper of Economic Policy|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1987/06/27/obituaries/arthur-f-burns-is-dead-at-83-a-shaper-of-economic-policy.html|publisher= New York Times}}</ref>\n* [[Mary M. Cohen]], social economist, writer\n* [[Peter Diamond]], Nobel Prize (2010)\n* [[Barry Eichengreen]], professor at University of California, Berkeley\n* [[Rashi Fein]], health economist\n* [[Martin Feldstein]], Harvard Professor; Chair of the [[Council of Economic Advisors]] in the Reagan Administration<ref name=\"THE TESTING OF MARTIN FELDSTEIN\">{{cite news|title=THE TESTING OF MARTIN FELDSTEIN|url=https://www.nytimes.com/1983/09/18/business/the-testing-of-martin-feldstein.html?pagewanted=all|publisher= New York Times}}</ref>\n* [[Amy Finkelstein]],  Professor of Economics at the Massachusetts Institute of Technology (MIT), the co-Director and research associate of the Public Economics Program at the [[National Bureau of Economic Research]], and the co-Scientific Director of J-PAL North America.<ref name=\"MIT Economist of Health Care Wins John Bates Clark Medal\">{{cite news|title=MIT Economist of Health Care Wins John Bates Clark Medal|url=https://www.chronicle.com/blogs/ticker/mit-economist-of-health-care-wins-john-bates-clark-medal/42712|publisher= The Chronicle of Higher Education}}</ref>\n* [[Stanley Fischer]], economist and the vice chair of the U.S. Federal Reserve System\n* [[Robert Fogel]], Nobel Prize (1993)\n* [[David D. Friedman]], son of Milton Friedman\n* [[Milton Friedman]], Nobel Prize (1976)<ref name=\"nobel1\">{{cite web |title=Milton Friedman on nobelprize.org |url=http://nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/economics/laureates/1976/ |year=1976 |publisher=Nobel Prize |accessdate=February 20, 2008}}</ref>\n* [[Alan Greenspan]], former Chair of the US [[Federal Reserve Bank]]<ref>{{cite news|author1= [[Benjamin M. Friedman]]|title=Chairman Greenspan\u2019s Legacy|url=http://www.nybooks.com/articles/archives/2008/mar/20/chairman-greenspans-legacy |work= [[New York Review of Books]] | volume = 55 | issue=4|date=March 20, 2008}}</ref>\n* [[John Harsanyi]], Nobel Prize (1994)\n* [[Leonid Hurwicz]], Nobel Prize (2007)\n* [[Daniel Kahneman]], Nobel Prize (2002)<ref name=\"Daniel Kahneman - Biographical\">{{cite web|title=Daniel Kahneman - Biographical|url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/economic-sciences/laureates/2002/kahneman-bio.html|publisher= Nobel Prize}}</ref>\n* [[Steven Kaplan (economist)|Steven Kaplan]]\n* [[Lawrence Klein]], Nobel Prize (1980)<ref name=\"Lawrence Klein (1920-2013)\">{{cite web|title=Lawrence Klein (1920-2013)|url=https://www.jewishvirtuallibrary.org/lawrence-klein|publisher= Jewish Virtual Library}}</ref>\n* [[Paul Krugman]], Nobel Prize (2008)<ref name=\"Paul Krugman - Facts\">{{cite web|title=Paul Krugman - Facts|url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/economic-sciences/laureates/2008/krugman-facts.html|publisher= Nobel Prize}}</ref>\n* [[Simon Kuznets]], Nobel Prize (1971)\n* [[Wassily Leontief]], Nobel Prize (1973)\n* [[Harry Markowitz]], Nobel Prize (1990)\n* [[Eric Maskin]], Nobel Prize (2007)<ref name=\"Eric S. Maskin - Facts\">{{cite web|title=Eric S. Maskin - Facts|url=https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/economic-sciences/laureates/2007/maskin-facts.html|publisher= Nobel Prize}}</ref>\n* [[Robert O. Mendelsohn]], environmental economist\n* [[Merton Miller]], Nobel Prize (1990)\n* [[Hyman Minsky]]\n* [[Franco Modigliani]], Nobel Prize (1985)\n* [[Toby Moskowitz]], financial economist<ref>{{cite book | last1 = Moskowitz | first1 = Tobias J. | last2 = Wertheim | first2 = L. Jon | title = Scorecasting: The Hidden Influences Behind How Sports Are Played and Games Are Won | publisher = Crown Archetype | year = 2011}}</ref>\n* [[Roger Myerson]], Nobel Prize (2007)\n* [[Russ Roberts]], host of ''[[EconTalk]]''\n* [[Alvin E. Roth]], Nobel Prize (2012)<ref>[https://www.nobelprize.org/nobel_prizes/economics/laureates/2012/ The Sveriges Riksbank Prize in Economic Sciences in Memory of Alfred Nobel 2012], [[Nobel Prize]] official site (accessed 2012-10-15).</ref>\n* [[Murray Rothbard]], writer, Austrian School economist, anarcho-capitalist, libertarian writer<ref>{{cite book |title=Biographical Dictionary of American Economists |publisher=Thoemmes |last=Lewis |first=David Charles |chapter=Rothbard, Murray Newton (1926\u20131995) |editor=Ross Emmett |year=2006 |isbn=1843711125}}</ref>\n* [[Nouriel Roubini]], Iranian-American macroeconomist<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.janera.com/janera_words.php?id%3D44 |title=Archived copy |accessdate=2008-02-27 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20080220041244/http://www.janera.com/janera_words.php?id=44 |archivedate=February 20, 2008 }}</ref>\n* [[Jeffrey Sachs]], director of the Earth Institute at Columbia University\n* [[Alexei Alexeyevich Abrikosov|Alexei Abrikosov]], condensed matter physics, Nobel Prize (2003)\n* [[Ralph Alpher]], background radiation, nucleosynthesis\n* [[John N. Bahcall]], astrophysicist\n* [[Hans Bethe]], nuclear phy