men's national team]]. The team competes in a variety of competitions, including the biennial [[FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup]] and [[African U-20 Cup of Nations for Women]], which is the top competitions for this age group. \n\nThe team as qualified for every edition of the [[FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup]] and have been runners-up twice, losing to [[Germany women's national under-20 football team| Germany]] on both occasions in [[2010 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup|2010]] and [[2014 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup|2014]].\n==Competitive record==\n===FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup record===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center;\"\n!colspan=10|[[FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup]]\n|-\n!Year\n!Result\n!Matches\n!Wins\n!Draws*\n!Losses\n!GF\n!GA\n|- bgcolor=\n|{{flagicon|CAN}} [[2002 FIFA U-19 Women's World Championship|2002]]||Group stage||3||0||1||2||2||5\n|-\n|{{flagicon|THA}} [[2004 FIFA U-19 Women's World Championship|2004]]||Quarter-finals||4||1||2||1||5||5\n|- bgcolor=\n|{{flagicon|RUS}} [[2006 FIFA U-20 Women's World Championship|2006]]||Quarter-finals||4||2||0||2||13||6\n|- bgcolor=\n|{{flagicon|CHI}} [[2008 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup|2008]]||Quarter-finals||4||2||2||2||8||5\n|- bgcolor=silver\n|{{flagicon|GER}} [[2010 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup|2010]]||'''Runners-up'''||'''6'''||'''3'''||'''2'''||'''0'''||'''5'''||'''6'''\n|- bgcolor=#9acdff\n|{{flagicon|JPN}} [[2012 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup|2012]]||'''Fourth place'''||'''6'''||'''3'''||'''1'''||'''2'''||'''9'''||'''7'''\n|- bgcolor=silver\n|{{flagicon|CAN}} [[2014 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup|2014]]||'''Runners-up'''||'''6'''||'''4'''||'''1'''||'''1'''||'''14'''||'''7'''\n|- \n|{{flagicon|PNG}} [[2016 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup|2016]]||Group stage||3||2||0||1||5||8\n|-\n|{{flagicon|FRA}} [[2018 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup|2018]]||Quarter-finals||4||1||1||2||3||4\n|-\n| {{flagicon|CRC}} {{flagicon|PAN}} [[2020 FIFA U-20 Women's World Cup|2020]] || colspan=7 | ''TBD''\n|-\n|'''Total'''||'''10/10'''||'''40'''|